{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"MIDIConnectionEvent()","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MIDIConnectionEvent/MIDIConnectionEvent","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_MIDI_API\">Web MIDI API</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MIDIConnectionEvent\"><code>MIDIConnectionEvent</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><em><code>MIDIConnectionEvent()</code></em></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MIDIConnectionEvent/port\"><code>port</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event\"><code>Event</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Web MIDI API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MIDIAccess\"><code>MIDIAccess</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MIDIInput\"><code>MIDIInput</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MIDIInputMap\"><code>MIDIInputMap</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MIDIMessageEvent\"><code>MIDIMessageEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MIDIOutput\"><code>MIDIOutput</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MIDIOutputMap\"><code>MIDIOutputMap</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MIDIPort\"><code>MIDIPort</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/requestMIDIAccess\"><code>Navigator.requestMIDIAccess()</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard secure\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Secure context:</strong> This feature is available only in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Secure_Contexts\">secure contexts</a> (HTTPS), in some or all <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">supporting browsers</a>.</p></div>\n<p>The <strong><code>MIDIConnectionEvent()</code></strong> constructor creates a new <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MIDIConnectionEvent\"><code>MIDIConnectionEvent</code></a> object. Typically this constructor is not used as events are created when a new port becomes available, and the object is passed to the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MIDIAccess/statechange_event\" title=\"statechange\"><code>statechange</code></a> event.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js-nolint notranslate\">new MIDIConnectionEvent(type)\nnew MIDIConnectionEvent(type, midiConnectionEventInit)\n</pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"type\"><code>type</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>A string with one of <code>\"connect\"</code> or <code>\"disconnect\"</code>.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"midiconnectioneventinit\"><code>midiConnectionEventInit</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>A dictionary including the following fields:</p>\n    <dl>\n      <dt id=\"port\"><code>port</code></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MIDIPort\"><code>MIDIPort</code></a> instance representing the port that has connected or disconnected.</p>\n      </dd>\n      <dt id=\"bubbles\"><code>bubbles</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>\n          A boolean value indicating whether the event bubbles. The default is\n          <code>false</code>.\n        </p>\n      </dd>\n      <dt id=\"cancelable\"><code>cancelable</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>\n          A boolean value indicating whether the event can be cancelled. The\n          default is <code>false</code>.\n        </p>\n      </dd>\n      <dt id=\"composed\"><code>composed</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>\n          A boolean value indicating whether the event will trigger listeners\n          outside of a shadow root (see <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event/composed\"><code>Event.composed</code></a> for more details). The\n          default is <code>false</code>.\n        </p>\n      </dd>\n    </dl>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://webaudio.github.io/web-midi-api/#dom-midiconnectionevent-constructor","title":"Web MIDI API"}],"query":"api.MIDIConnectionEvent.MIDIConnectionEvent"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.MIDIConnectionEvent.MIDIConnectionEvent","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MIDIConnectionEvent/MIDIConnectionEvent/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The MIDIConnectionEvent() constructor creates a new MIDIConnectionEvent object. Typically this constructor is not used as events are created when a new port becomes available, and the object is passed to the statechange event.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-13T05:54:54.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/midiconnectionevent/midiconnectionevent","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/midiconnectionevent/midiconnectionevent/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/b7556b71e1fc3e89057671b372871e9f33d3f0b8","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/MIDIConnectionEvent","title":"MIDIConnectionEvent"},{"uri":"/